The executive secretary of the Nigerian Christian Pilgrims Commission (NCPC), Rev Tor Uja, has expressed sadness over the death of his Personal Assistant on Media Matters and Special Duties, Pastor Fred Romeo Obika. Uja who disclosed this in a statement issued to journalists in Abuja, described the death of Pastor Obika as shocking. The executive secretary who explained that the deceased passed away on April 17, 2019 after a brief illness, said he was a committed patriot who pursued his beliefs with uncommon zeal. He said the commission would sorely miss the deceased, especially at this time when his services were most needed. “I want to express our heartfelt condolence to the family of  Pastor Obika on this great and irreparable loss,” he said. He explained that though painful, it was the will of God and asked the family to be comforted by the Lord Almighty.